bounds. This is due to
the `GetConstantIntRange`
lambda in
`getArgumentAccessInfo`
attempting to construct a
`ConstantRange` from a
`Length` value that is
not a
`ConstantInt`.\n\n2.
**Analyzing `opt`'s
Log**: The backtrace
shows that the failure
occurs when
`ConstantRangeList::inser
t` is called. The
`GetConstantIntRange`
lambda is responsible for
constructing the
`ConstantRange` objects
passed to
`ConstantRangeList::inser
t`.\n\n3. **Root Cause
Analysis**: The
`GetConstantIntRange`
lambda assumes that
`Length` is a
`ConstantInt` and
attempts to compute a
range using its signed
extended value. If
`Length` is not a
