the `ConstantRange` is
only constructed when
`Length` is a valid
`ConstantInt` with a
strictly positive
value.\n\n5.
**Conclusion**: This fix
ensures that the
`GetConstantIntRange`
lambda does not attempt
to construct invalid
`ConstantRange` objects,
preventing the assertion
failure in
`ConstantRangeList::inser
t`.",
